- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a benchmark suite for parity games and discusses their structural properties.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also likely as parity games are often used in game theory and the paper discusses how the benchmarks were generated.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is another possible category as parity games are closely related to temporal logic and the paper discusses the structural properties of parity games.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as parity games are used in model checking and verification, which are important topics in AI.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the implementation and availability of the benchmark suite.
